%S A393909 1,1,2,1228,14089656148992,
%T A393909 50346839734076286938886836265405905350164480
%N A393909 Number of planar embedding isomorphism classes of the n-Dorogovtsev-Goltsev-Mendes graph.
%C A393909 These counts allow the mirror image as an isomorphism.
%C A393909 Using the indexing convention DGM(0) = P_2.
%C A393909 a(6) has 136 decimal digits and a(7) has 412 decimal digits. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Mar 03 2026
%H A393909 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A393909/b393909.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..7</a>
%H A393909 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Dorogovtsev-Goltsev-MendesGraph.html">Dorogovtsev-Goltsev-Mendes Graph</a>.
%H A393909 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/PlanarEmbedding.html">Planar Embedding</a>.
%F A393909 a(n) = (b(n)^3 + 2*b(n) + 3*c(n)*b(n))/12 for n >= 2, where b(n) = Product_{k=1..n} k^(3^(n-k)), c(n) = Product_{k=1..n} k^((3^(n-k)+1)/2). - _Andrew Howroyd_, Mar 03 2026
%o A393909 (PARI) a(n) = if(n<2, 1, my(b=prod(k=2, n, k^(3^(n-k))), c=prod(k=2, n, k^((3^(n-k)+1)/2))); (b^3 + 2*b + 3*c*b)/12) \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Mar 03 2026
%K A393909 nonn
%O A393909 0,3
%A A393909 _Eric W. Weisstein_, Mar 02 2026
%E A393909 a(4) onward from _Andrew Howroyd_, Mar 03 2026
